'''Jaminton Leandro Campaz''' (born 24 May 2000) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Rosario Central]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.futbolred.com/seleccion-colombia/jaminton-campaz-hablo-de-su-actualidad-con-tolima-y-de-la-preparacion-de-la-seleccion-sub-17-al-mundial-58692|title='He trabajado bien en Tolima, pero debo mantener humildad': Jaminton|first=Casa Editorial El|last=Tiempo|website=futbolred.com |date=2 May 2017 }}</ref>

==Club career==
Campaz joined [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Grêmio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Grêmio]] from [[Deportes Tolima]] in August 2021, having signed a contract until December 2025.<ref>{{cite web |title=Colombiano Jaminton Campaz é o novo reforço do Tricolor |url=https://gremio.net/noticias/detalhes/24580/colombiano-jaminton-campaz-e-o-novo-reforco-do-tricolor |website=Grêmio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense |access-date=24 August 2021 |language=pt |date=24 August 2021}}</ref>

==International career==
Campaz was selected for the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]] for [[2021 Copa América]] and made his debut on 17 June 2021 in a match against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=560518|title=Colombia v Venezuela game report|date=17 June 2021|accessdate=11 August 2021}}</ref>

